# Marketing Sales Analysis





📌 Overview

This project provides an in-depth analysis of marketing sales data using Python. The goal is to explore key trends, build a predictive model using linear regression, and evaluate its performance.

📂 Dataset

Dataset Name: Marketing Sales Data

Source: Dataset Link

Format: CSV

Key Features: Includes sales, advertising spend, and other relevant marketing metrics

🛠️ Tools & Libraries

pandas – Data manipulation and analysis

numpy – Numerical computations

matplotlib & seaborn – Data visualization

statsmodels – Statistical modeling and regression analysis

📌 Table of Contents

1️⃣ Import & Load Data

2️⃣ Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

3️⃣ Model Building

4️⃣ Results & Insights

5️⃣ Key Findings & Business Impact

1️⃣ Import & Load Data

import pandas as pd
data = pd.read_csv("data/marketing_sales_data.csv")
data.head()

2️⃣ Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

📊 Checking missing values, dataset dimensions, and visualizing key relationships.

3️⃣ Model Building

📈 Using statsmodels to fit a linear regression model and analyze marketing strategies' impact on sales.

4️⃣ Results & Insights

✅ Validated statistical model with properly analyzed residuals and key coefficients.

5️⃣ Key Findings & Business Impact

💡 Optimizing marketing spend to maximize sales performance.

🚀 How to Run the Project

git clone https://github.com/your-username/marketing-sales-analysis.git
cd marketing-sales-analysis
pip install -r requirements.txt
jupyter notebook

